{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide funding for greater holistic dementia care after the covid-19 pandemic.",
        "additional_details": "Since covid-19 dementia care at home has been one of the hardest things to sustain without negative effect upon the person diagnosed and the carers, it is usually acted upon out of moral duty, the aim is to provide a bridge in the gap between homecare, holistic therapy and external agency, funding needs to be provided to local authorities to use at their discretion to external agency who can provide validated Holistic engaging therapy",
        "background": "Provide funding for the health and social care sector so that the funds can provide holistic homecare therapy such as active minds, befriending and a wellbeing device from external services in addition to other home care.",
